1. Collection Interface: The root interface of the collection hierarchy. It declares basic operations like add, remove, clear, anc size.
2. List Interface: An ordered collection. Lists can contain duplicate elements.
3. Set Interface: A collection that cannot contain duplicate elements.
4. Queue Interface: A collection used for holding elements in FIFO prior to process
5. Map Interface: Not a true Collection, but part of the Collections Framework. Map store
                  key-value pairs. Keys are unique, but different keys can map to
                  the same value.
